- 2.0.2 | Feb 25 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] SYN flood protection: SYNFLOOD chain rate-limits inbound TCP SYN packets
      via iptables limit module; configurable rate/burst thresholds, LOG +
      DROP for excess, dual-stack support (conf.apf, bt.rules, .ca.def)
[New] SMTP outbound blocking: SMTP_BLOCK restricts outbound SMTP (ports 25,
      465, 587) to whitelisted users/groups; root always allowed;
      SMTP_ALLOWUSER/SMTP_ALLOWGROUP exemptions with runtime --gid-owner
      detection; works independently of EGF toggle (conf.apf, cports.common)
[New] Temporary allow/deny with per-entry TTL: apf -ta/-td HOST TTL adds
      time-limited trust entries; supports seconds/minutes/hours/days (300,
      5m, 1h, 7d); automatic cron expiry; list with --templ, flush with
      --tempf; block escalation auto-promotes repeat temp denies to permanent
      via PERMBLOCK_COUNT/PERMBLOCK_INTERVAL (apf, functions.apf, conf.apf,
      cron.d.apf, .ca.def)
[New] Custom hook scripts: hook_pre.sh/hook_post.sh sourced before/after
      iptables rules; activated by chmod 750; all APF variables available;
      preserved across upgrades (firewall, importconf)
[New] Silent IP blocking: silent_ips.rules drops all traffic to/from listed
      addresses with no logging; IPv4/IPv6 supported; entries validated with
      valid_host(); preserved across upgrades (firewall, importconf)
[New] Search CLI: apf -g PATTERN searches iptables rules (IPv4/IPv6), ipset
      sets, and trust files; case-insensitive (apf, functions.apf)
[New] Per-port connection limiting via xt_connlimit: IG_TCP_CLIMIT and
      IG_UDP_CLIMIT config variables with port:limit pairs, port range
      support, and VNET per-IP binding (conf.apf, cports.common)
[New] ipset 7-field format: per-list refresh interval and max entry count;
      IPSET_REFRESH global default; per-list interval tracking via
      .ipset.timestamps; backward-compatible auto-migration from 4-field
      and 5-field formats (functions.apf, ipset.rules, conf.apf)
[New] download_url(): unified download helper with curl primary, wget
      fallback; redirect following, 10s connect / 60s total timeout, 3
      retries; all download sites migrated; check_deps() warns when
      neither available (functions.apf)
[New] Advanced trust syntax in CLI: apf -a/-d/-ta/-td/-u now accept
      proto:flow:port:ip format (e.g., "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8") for
      protocol/direction/port-scoped trust rules; live iptables insertion
      via trust_entry_rule(); bare IP removal also removes advanced entries
      containing that IP; duplicate detection, IPv6 bracket syntax, port
      ranges, and temp trust TTL markers all supported (functions.apf)
[New] validate_config(): startup validation for TCP_STOP/UDP_STOP/ALL_STOP
      stop targets, SYNFLOOD rate/burst format, connlimit entry syntax, and
      SYSCTL_SYNCOOKIES/SYSCTL_OVERFLOW conflict; clear error messages
      instead of cryptic iptables failures (functions.apf, apf)
[New] FQDN pre-resolution in trust system: hostnames are resolved to IP
      addresses via getent before loading into iptables; supports multiple
      A/AAAA records, IPv6 (when USE_IPV6=1), configurable timeout via
      FQDN_TIMEOUT; resolved= metadata in trust file comments enables
      removal without DNS; refresh (apf -e) re-resolves FQDNs; works in
      CLI (-a/-d/-ta/-td/-u) and bulk load (functions.apf, conf.apf,
      internals.conf, .ca.def; 20 tests)
[New] --rules: dump active iptables rules to stdout for piping/scripting;
      uses -S format consistent across nft/legacy backends; includes IPv6
      when USE_IPV6=1 (apf, functions.apf)
[New] --info: firewall status summary with sections for status (active state,
      rules, chains), trust system (allow/deny/temp counts, ban expiry, block
      escalation, FQDN resolution), filtering (stop targets, inbound/outbound
      ports, packet sanity, connlimit, SYN flood, SMTP blocking), subsystems
      (fast load, RAB, VNET, Docker compat, ipset, GRE, remote block lists),
      and logging (log file, log drops, trim, recent entries)
      (apf, functions.apf)
[New] --lookup HOST: check if host exists in trust files (allow, deny, global
      allow, global deny) without searching iptables/ipset rules; exits 0 if
      found, 1 if not found (apf, functions.apf)
[New] -h/--help: explicit help handler exits 0; previously no args exited 1
      (apf)
[New] --validate/--check: validate config without starting firewall; checks
      stop targets, rate formats, connlimit syntax (apf, functions.apf)
[New] --list-allow/--list-deny (--la/--ld): display trust file entries with
      comments and blank lines stripped (apf, functions.apf)
[New] --dump-config: self-documenting alias for -o/--ovars (apf)

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] install.sh: fix chmod -R 640 breaking subdirectory traversal;
      use find to set dirs=750, files=640, then explicit executable perms
      (install.sh)
[Fix] install.sh: suppress "Device does not exist" stderr from vnetgen
      during install (install.sh)
[Fix] importconf: guard vnet/*.rules glob to prevent "cannot stat" error
      on fresh or non-VNET installs (importconf, files/extras/importconf)
[Fix] importconf: suppress stderr noise from conf.apf sourcing during
      config import (importconf, files/extras/importconf)
[Fix] files/extras/importconf: use INSTALL_PATH variable default pattern
      (files/extras/importconf)
[New] install.sh: auto-detect default network interface on fresh install;
      sets IFACE_UNTRUSTED when not eth0 (install.sh)
[New] install.sh: show default routed interface and additional interfaces
      during install; contextual output when no default route found
      (install.sh)
[Change] importconf: clarify message on same-version reinstall
      (importconf, files/extras/importconf)
[Change] install.sh: optimize sed path replacement with grep -rl
      pre-filter; skip files that don't contain /etc/apf (install.sh)
[Change] install.sh: add error handling for mkdir and file copy
      (install.sh)
[Change] install.sh: remove unnecessary sleep 1 (install.sh)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove(): anchor comment cleanup sed pattern to prevent
      over-deletion; '# added 192.0.2.1 ' no longer matches 192.0.2.10
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust(): change duplicate check from grep -Fw to grep -Fx for
      exact full-line match; prevents FQDN substring false positives
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] check_block_escalation(): anchor grep pattern with ^ and escape dots
      to prevent IP prefix collisions in block history (functions.apf)
[Fix] escalate_to_permanent(): anchor sed patterns to comment format, use
      % delimiter for CIDR safety, replace subprocesses with bash parameter
      expansion (functions.apf)
[Fix] expire_temp_entries(): anchor sed pattern to '# added IP ' prefix to
      prevent substring over-deletion of temp trust comments (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove(): spec-based iptables rule deletion replaces racy
      line-number approach; tracks removal status and returns 1 when host
      not found (functions.apf)
[Fix] lgate_mac(): use $VF_LGATE instead of undefined $LGATE_MAC; gateway
      MAC filtering was non-functional (functions.apf)
[Fix] expirebans(): fix $ip loop variable shadowing global iproute2 path;
      replace unquoted array expansion with IFS read to prevent globbing;
      add date parse error handling; skip ttl= entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] ipset_migrate_rules(): add 5-field (v2.0.1) to 7-field migration;
      5-field entries were silently dropped on upgrade (functions.apf)
[Fix] glob_allow_download()/glob_deny_download(): validate entries with
      valid_host() instead of raw file copy (functions.apf)
[Fix] Escape dots in IP addresses used in sed patterns across
      cli_trust_remove(), expirebans(), expire_temp_entries() (functions.apf)
[Fix] importconf: preserve preroute.rules/postroute.rules and hook script
      permissions during upgrade (importconf)
[Fix] SMTP_BLK: add chain-exists guard for VNET re-sourcing; add to Docker
      compat flush chain list; warn on empty SMTP_PORTS (cports.common,
      functions.apf)
[Fix] .ca.def preamble: add missing defaults for SYSCTL_CONNTRACK_*,
      DOCKER_COMPAT, IG_ICMPV6_TYPES, EG_ICMPV6_TYPES; prevents empty
      values on upgrade from pre-2.0.1 (.ca.def)
[Fix] Bash 4.2+ ${var,,}/${var^^} reverted to tr-based case conversion for
      CentOS 6 compatibility (cports.common, internals.conf)
[Fix] Fast load IPv4 restore failure now flushes partial rules before
      falling through to full load, matching IPv6 failure behavior (apf)
[Fix] Unknown CLI options now exit with code 1 instead of 0 (apf)
[Fix] Quote $INSTALL_PATH in 32+ locations across apf, firewall, and
      functions.apf to handle paths with spaces
[Fix] Strip control characters from trust comment field to prevent line
      injection in allow/deny hosts files (functions.apf)
[Fix] install.sh: cd to script directory and verify source files before
      installing; remove pre-install rm -rf to prevent data loss on failure
      (install.sh)
[Fix] refresh(): populate REFRESH_TEMP from trust files instead of
      iptables-save parsing; move temp file creation past MD5 early-exit
      to prevent orphaned files (functions.apf)
[Fix] flush(): remove /etc/cron.d/refresh.apf on firewall stop; prevents
      refresh into a stopped firewall (functions.apf)
[Fix] Add missing local declarations to 10 functions to prevent global
      scope pollution (functions.apf)
[Fix] Rename head() to apf_banner() to stop shadowing /usr/bin/head in
      sourced scripts (apf)
[Fix] Propagate cli_trust/cli_trust_temp return codes to CLI exit status;
      apf -a/-d/-ta/-td now exit 1 on failure (apf)
[Fix] REFRESH_TEMP now protects bare IPv6 trust entries during refresh;
      change case filter from *:* to *=* so IPv6 addresses are not
      excluded while advanced trust entries remain correctly skipped
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] Install FLOW document to doc/ directory alongside README; resolves
      missing file referenced by README documentation (install.sh)
[Fix] Migrate EG_DROP_CMD from space-separated (pre-2.0.2) to
      comma-separated format during upgrade via importconf (importconf)
[Fix] install.sh: display detected listening ports during upgrade installs;
      previously only shown on fresh installs (install.sh)
[Fix] validate_config(): add validation for ICMP_LIM (rate format), LOG_LEVEL,
      LOG_TARGET, LOG_RATE (integer), SYSCTL_CONNTRACK (integer); reject
      non-numeric PERMBLOCK_COUNT/PERMBLOCK_INTERVAL (functions.apf)
[Fix] validate_config(): reject empty IFACE_UNTRUSTED, invalid RAB_PSCAN_LEVEL,
      non-numeric RAB_HITCOUNT/RAB_TIMER, RAB_TIMER=0, SYNFLOOD_BURST=0, and
      LOG_RATE=0; RAB checks gated on RAB=1; defense-in-depth default branch
      in firewall RAB_PSCAN_LEVEL case (functions.apf, firewall)
[Fix] cl_cports(): clear EG_DROP_CMD between VNET iterations; prevents
      command-owner rules from leaking across per-IP rule files (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove(): reject empty argument with error message; prevents
      confusing double output when apf -u called with no host (functions.apf)
[Fix] Quote $IFACE_UNTRUSTED in sysctl.rules redirect paths and internals.conf
      ip addr list calls; aligns with project variable quoting convention
      (sysctl.rules, internals.conf)
[Fix] logrotate: add copytruncate directive to preserve log file inode for
      external tail -f consumers (logrotate.d.apf)
[Fix] trim(): replace mv with cat+rm to preserve file inode; prevents inode
      change when trust files are trimmed (functions.apf)
[Change] trust_hosts(): cache file content in single read; tighten pass 3/4
      grep filters to target only 4-field and 5-field entries respectively;
      eliminates redundant file reads (functions.apf)
[Fix] Replace deprecated -a test operator with && in OpenVZ detection
      (internals.conf)
[Fix] Quote all dot-source paths to prevent word splitting on paths with
      spaces (internals.conf, firewall, conf.apf, vnetgen.def)
[Fix] Hoist local declarations out of loops in validate_config(); remove
      redundant _vc_burst variable (functions.apf)
[Fix] Add -r flag to all read commands to prevent backslash interpretation
      (apf, functions.apf, sysctl.rules, bt.rules)
[Change] Extract inline regex patterns to named variables in validation
      functions for portability and readability (functions.apf, gretunnel.sh)
[Fix] Fast load failure now skips snapshot save to prevent overwriting
      working snapshot with broken/partial state (apf)
[Fix] Firewall script exit code checked; failure aborts start cleanly
      instead of saving partial snapshot (apf)
[Fix] Temp file cleanup on signal: global tracking prevents orphaned
      files in install directory on SIGTERM/SIGINT (functions.apf, apf)
[Change] Remove unused action_all variable from trust_entry_rule()
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] trim(): exclude blank lines from data line count (functions.apf)
[Fix] expirebans(): use local variable instead of modifying global
      SET_EXPIRE (functions.apf)
[Fix] --gre-up/--gre-down report disabled state instead of silently
      exiting (apf)
[New] snapshot_save(): atomic fast load snapshot writes via mktemp+mv;
      validates iptables-save exit code and output (non-empty, contains
      table markers); IPv6 snapshot failure non-fatal to IPv4; backend
      marker written by snapshot_save for both save-side callers
      (functions.apf, apf)
[Fix] Fast load restore validates snapshot before iptables-restore:
      empty or invalid snapshots (missing *table markers) fall back to
      full load instead of silently loading no rules (apf)
[Change] expirebans(): prefer structured addedtime=EPOCH markers over
      positional awk date extraction; legacy fallback for pre-2.0.2
      entries without addedtime=; fix orphaned comment lines left behind
      when bare IP was removed (functions.apf)
[New] cli_trust permanent entries now include addedtime=EPOCH marker in
      comment lines for reliable ban expiry; consistent with temp trust
      expire= pattern; backward compatible (functions.apf)

  -- Changes --

[Change] File-based flock mutex: replace FD-based exec/flock with file-based
      gate; noclobber + PID fallback; EXIT trap releases lock on signal;
      trust CLI operations (-a, -d, -u, -ta, -td) acquire lock to prevent
      races with concurrent cron operations (apf, functions.apf)
[Change] ESTABLISHED,RELATED state tracking moved earlier in INPUT chain;
      established connections now fast-path past VNET, port filtering, and
      logging (firewall)
[Change] Fast load uptime threshold raised from 5 to 10 minutes (apf)
[Change] Consolidate 3 cron files into single cron.d.apf with daily restart,
      hourly ipset refresh, and per-minute temp expiry (cron.d.apf, install.sh)
[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; reduces load time from
      minutes to seconds for large block lists (functions.apf)
[Change] Performance and code consolidation: replace subprocess chains
      (echo|tr|awk|grep) with bash builtins across all hot paths; unify
      duplicated code (trust_hosts, dlist_download, _icmp_filter,
      expand_port, trust_parse_fields, tosroute); modernize string tests
      and remove unnecessary $(echo $var) wrappers (functions.apf,
      cports.common, bt.rules, firewall, vnetgen, main.vnet, sysctl.rules,
      install.sh, internals.conf)
[Change] VNET: replace fork-heavy parsing with builtins and glob patterns;
      fix ifconfig detection; add variable quoting; use conditional default
      for INSTALL_PATH (main.vnet, vnetgen)
[Change] help() pass 2: remove silent options (-st, --temp-expire) from display;
      show readable names (--temp-list, --dump-config, --list-allow) over
      cryptic aliases (--templ, --ovars, --la); add --rules, --info, --lookup;
      update -l description to "view in editor"; all hidden aliases still work
      in dispatcher (functions.apf, apf.8, README, README.md)
[Change] cl_cports(): reset SMTP and connlimit variables for VNET per-IP
      consistency (functions.apf)
[Change] Drop Ubuntu 22.04 from CI matrix; redundant with 20.04+24.04
      (smoke-test.yml)
[Fix] sysctl.rules: fix wrong proc paths for secure_redirects, send_redirects,
      and proxy_arp; per-interface sysctls require conf/all/ prefix — settings
      were silently never applied due to error suppression (sysctl.rules)
[Change] trust_hosts: replace four-pass grep cascade with single-pass loop
      and delegate advanced syntax to trust_entry_rule(); eliminates ~210
      lines of duplicated field extraction and iptables logic (C-002)
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] trust_hosts: anchor comment filter to line start (grep -v '^#')
      preventing false matches on entries containing '#' (F-019)
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] trust_hosts: eliminate grep -v tcp/udp classification that could
      misclassify entries containing protocol substrings (F-020)
      (functions.apf)

  -- Documentation --

[New] uninstall.sh: removes all system-wide artifacts; prompts before removing
      install directory and logs (uninstall.sh)
[New] install.sh: post-install dependency warnings for iptables, ip, modprobe;
      non-fatal for chroot/container builds (install.sh)
[New] README/README.md: section 2.4 Uninstallation (README, README.md)
[Fix] .ca.def: DLIST_*_URL variables now preserve user customizations on
      upgrade; preamble defaults + variable expansion in template (.ca.def)
[New] Man page: apf.8 section 8, all CLI operations, trust system overview,
      configuration reference, installed to /usr/share/man/man8/ (apf.8,
      install.sh)
[New] FLOW.md/FLOW: standalone order-of-operations document with INPUT chain
      precedence table and fast/full load conditions
[Change] README/README.md: modernize headers; add Quick Start section;
      reorganize feature list; add documentation for connlimit, uid-based
      egress, ICMPv6 types, SMTP blocking, temporary trust, hooks, silent
      IPs, search CLI, and firewall order of operations
[Change] conf.apf: correct DOCKER_COMPAT comment; improve IPT_LOCK docs
      (conf.apf)
[Change] Remove untested Debian 10/11 from supported platforms list (README)
[Fix] help() missing -st alias: add -st to status line help text to match
      case dispatcher (functions.apf)
[Fix] FLOW: add missing SYNFLOOD entry to INPUT chain precedence table;
      renumber entries 23-48 to match FLOW.md (FLOW)
[Fix] README/README.md: correct backup path format from DDMMYY-UTIME to
      DDMMYYYY-EPOCH to match install.sh date format; sync -e/--refresh
      description with help() wording (README, README.md)
[Fix] .ca.def: sync IPT_LOCK_SUPPORT/IPT_LOCK_TIMEOUT comments with
      conf.apf (includes version range and compatibility notes)
[Fix] Man page: --rules output format corrected from "iptables-save" to
      "iptables -S" (apf.8)
[Fix] conf.apf: document NFLOG as accepted LOG_TARGET value alongside LOG
      and ULOG (conf.apf, apf.8, README)
[Fix] README: troubleshooting corrected from 'apf -l | grep' (opens editor)
      to 'apf --rules | grep' (stdout-pipeable) (README)
[New] .dockerignore: exclude .git, .github, .claude, audit-output, and
      working files from Docker build context
[Change] Makefile: override sequential tier targets (test-all, test-modern,
      test-legacy, test-deep-legacy) to continue on failure and report
      combined exit code instead of stopping on first failure
[Change] nft backend detection: extract detect_ipt_backend() to eliminate
      duplicated iptables --version parsing in snapshot_save() and fast
      load path; sets global IPT_BACKEND (functions.apf, apf)
[Fix] Cron lifecycle: clean runtime-created refresh.apf and apf_develmode
      cron entries during install and uninstall; prevents stale cron jobs
      from persisting across reinstalls (install.sh, uninstall.sh)
[Change] glob trust download: extract glob_trust_download() helper to
      eliminate duplicated download/parse/validate logic between
      glob_allow_download() and glob_deny_download(); both become
      one-line wrappers (functions.apf)
[Change] dlist chain loading: extract dlist_load_hosts() helper to unify
      chain creation, valid_ip_cidr validation, LOG+DROP rules, and
      INPUT/OUTPUT attachment; dlist_php_hosts, dlist_dshield_hosts,
      dlist_spamhaus_hosts become one-line wrappers (functions.apf)
[Change] pkt_sanity: extract pkt_sanity_flags() helper to replace ~170
      lines of unrolled TCP flag pair checks with loop calls; unifies
      IPv4 IN/OUT_SANITY and IPv6 IN/OUT_SANITY6; preserves RAB
      integration and LOG behavior (functions.apf, bt.rules)
[Change] ipset: extract ipset_populate_set() to deduplicate awk filter,
      restore, and count logic between ipset_load() and ipset_update();
      uses awk set variable instead of shell interpolation in awk body;
      sets _IPSET_COUNT global to avoid subshell (functions.apf)
[Change] Remove dead IN_IF/OUT_IF variables from internals.conf; replace
      command head shim with plain head in functions.apf now that head()
      has been renamed to apf_banner() (internals.conf, functions.apf)
[Change] cli_trust: extract _sanitize_comment() and _trust_action_target()
      helpers; replaces 6 copy-pasted comment sanitization blocks and 4
      duplicated DENY/ALLOW→iptables action mappings (functions.apf)
[Change] cli_trust_remove: extract _resolve_fqdn_metadata(),
      _trust_remove_ip_rules(), and _trust_remove_advanced_entries()
      helpers; deduplicates FQDN metadata lookup (2 sites), 12-rule
      iptables deletion + spec-based cleanup (2 sites), and advanced
      entry recursive cleanup (2 sites) (functions.apf)
[Change] expiry: extract _parse_temp_comment() helper to deduplicate
      IP/TTL/epoch extraction from temp trust comment lines across
      expire_temp_entries(), list_temp_entries(), and
      flush_temp_entries(); document error suppression rationale and
      dual-track parsing in expirebans() (functions.apf)
[Change] bt.rules: extract _log_drop() and _rab_log() helpers to
      replace inline LOG_DROP/RAB_LOG_HIT check+action patterns;
      adopted at SANITY INV, PZERO, PZERO6, SYNFLOOD, IDENT, MCAST,
      and MCAST6 blocks (functions.apf, bt.rules)
[Change] bt.rules: unify IPv4/IPv6 sanity/frag/pzero chains via
      _sanity_inv_rules(), _frag_udp_rules(), _pzero_rules() helpers;
      merges separate IPv4 and IPv6 PKT_SANITY blocks into one
      structure with parameterized ipt function and chain names;
      preserves IPv4-only tcp-option 64/128 rules and IPv6-only
      RAB_SANITY_FLAGS on INVALID (bt.rules)
[Change] cports: extract _port_filter_loop() helper to deduplicate four
      identical IG/EG TCP/UDP port-filtering loops into parameterized
      calls (cports.common)
[Change] cports: extract _uid_filter_loop() helper to deduplicate
      EG_TCP_UID/EG_UDP_UID blocks (cports.common)
[Change] cports: consolidate 7 separate EGF guards into single outer
      block; reduces redundant conditional checks (cports.common)
[Change] cports: replace hardcoded NDP type loops (133 134 135 136) with
      $NDP_TYPES constant defined in internals.conf; adopted in
      cports.common and bt.rules MCAST6 NDP exemption (internals.conf,
      cports.common, bt.rules)
[Change] ipset: extract _ipset_parse_entry() and _ipset_resolve_data()
      helpers to deduplicate field parsing, validation, URL download, and
      maxelem capping shared between ipset_load() and ipset_update()
      (functions.apf)
[Change] firewall: extract _verify_iface_route() helper to deduplicate
      interface route verification for IFACE_UNTRUSTED and IFACE_TRUSTED
      (firewall)
[Change] Document error suppression rationale: restore_external_baseline
      non-APF chain tolerance, flush_apf_chains conditional existence
      checks, ipset non-blocking download policy, dlist backup restore
      policy (functions.apf)
[Fix] expirebans()/expire_temp_entries()/flush_temp_entries(): defer
      cli_trust_remove calls until after iteration loop completes; avoids
      modifying trust files via sed while reading them (functions.apf)
[Fix] refresh(): exit 0 when trust rules unchanged; no-change is a
      successful no-op, not an error (functions.apf)
[Fix] Root importconf missing EG_DROP_CMD space-to-comma migration that
      existed in files/extras/importconf; users upgrading from pre-2.0.2
      now get consistent comma-separated format (importconf)
[Change] apf_banner(): add "v2" qualifier to GPL notice to match file
      header and license (apf)
[Change] internals.conf: add standard copyright header block matching
      other APF source files (internals.conf)
[Change] Document deliberate -a/-d exit code propagation; cli_trust
      failure now exits 1 instead of silent 0 (apf)

  -- Test Suite --

[New] 11 new test files: 21-refactor-regression, 22-uid-egress,
      23-devel-fastload, 24-vnet, 25-connlimit, 26-hook-search-silent,
      27-temp-trust, 28-synflood, 29-block-escalation, 30-advanced-trust-cli,
      31-fqdn-trust (487 tests total across 31 files)
[New] LOG_DROP=0 negative tests: verify SYNFLOOD and SMTP_BLK chains omit LOG
      rules when LOG_DROP is disabled (28-synflood.bats, 22-uid-egress.bats)
[New] Hook execution order tests: verify hook_pre.sh runs before trust chains
      and hook_post.sh runs after default DROP policies (26-hook-search-silent.bats)
[New] Hook environment test: verify hooks have access to $IPT and $INSTALL_PATH
      variables (26-hook-search-silent.bats)
[New] Hook error handling tests: verify firewall continues loading when
      hook_pre.sh or hook_post.sh fails (26-hook-search-silent.bats)
[New] Search special character tests: verify apf -g handles dots, brackets,
      and dash-prefixed patterns without crashing (26-hook-search-silent.bats)
[New] 32-cli-help.bats: tests for -h/--help, --dump-config, --validate/--check,
      --la/--ld, section headers in help output (32-cli-help.bats)
[Fix] Hook ordering test: CentOS 6 iptables 1.4.7 compat — use protocol-
      specific DROP anchor instead of catch-all (26-hook-search-silent.bats)
[New] Test parallelization: --parallel [N] flag splits across N containers;
      3x speedup (run-tests.sh, Makefile)
[Change] Migrate test infrastructure to batsman shared framework via git
      submodule at tests/infra; replaces monolithic Dockerfiles with two-phase
      base+project builds, replaces 254-line run-tests.sh and 91-line Makefile
      with thin wrappers, replaces standalone CI with batsman reusable workflow;
      drops untested ubuntu2204 target, adds rocky10 as EXTRA tier
      (tests/Dockerfile*, tests/run-tests.sh, tests/Makefile, smoke-test.yml)
[New] ipset migration edge-case tests: missing ipset.rules early return,
      comment/blank-line preservation, mixed 4-field + 5-field in one pass
